The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | MphasiS to buy AIG division
                                                                                                               MphasiS to buy AIG division
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, Aug. 12: Troubled American International Group (AIG) has managed to get buyers for two of its units  India-based IT services wing AIG Systems Solutions Private Ltd and Hong Kong-based consumer finance firm AIG Finance Ltd.         
	Last years global financial crisis had floored AIG, and the company had to be bailed out by the US government.         
	MphasiS Ltd of Bangalore has agreed to buy AIG Systems Solutions for an undisclosed amount.         
	China Construction Bank (Asia)  the second biggest lender in China  will buy AIG Finance for $70 million. The deal includes the repayment of intra-group debt and deposits of about $557 million. Deutsche Bank AG had advised AIG on the transaction.        
	AIG Systems Solutions, which provides IT services to AIG firms globally, has more than 800 staff at its facilities in Chennai and Calcutta. Electronic Data Systems Corp, a Hewlett-Packard unit, owns MphasiS.         
	Indian officials of AIG declined to comment on the sale.        
	AIG Finance  a wholly owned subsidiary  is a restricted licence bank in Hong Kong. The company has more than 500,000 customers, total loans of 4.8 billion Hong Kong dollars ($619 million) and a retail deposit balance of $1 billion Hong Kong dollars. It employs over 350 people.        
	AIG had yesterday said AIG Financial Products had completed the sale of its energy and infrastructure investment assets for about $1.9 billion.                                                                                                                                                            
